# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the user is
#   expected to use the package environment.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if delegates have different platforms/python versions,
#   it might cause dependency conflicts.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#   poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains specific versions of dependencies
#pdm.lock

